params.name: vocab_file
params.description: The file containing the byte rewriting rules.

params.name: unk_token
params.description: The unknown token. A token that is not in the vocabulary cannot be converted to an ID and is set to be thistoken instead.

params.name: pad_token
params.description: The token used for padding, for example when batching sequences of different lengths.

params.name: extra_ids
params.description: Add a number of extra ids added to the end of the vocabulary for use as sentinels. These tokens areaccessible as id{%d}> where {%d} is a number between 0 and extra_ids-1. Extra tokens areindexed from the end of the vocabulary up to beginning ( is the last token in the vocabularylike in ByT5 preprocessing seehere).

params.name: additional_special_tokens
params.description: Additional special tokens used by the tokenizer.
